                            Font Preferences Editor

        The Font preferences editor gives you complete control over the
type and size of fonts used by the icons on the Workbench screen, the
default system font and the screen text font. By default, all three of
these use the standard Topaz 8 system font, but you can easily change them
to just about any size or type of font that is installed in the Fonts
directory on your Workbench disk. Be very careful when changing fonts,
however - using a 64 point font for your Workbench icons may sound very
pretty, but your Workbench screen will become rather confused.


